parameters: \n< Guild Master >So, we missed collecting the goblin's nose.

\n< Serena >I wasn't really into it from the
beginning.

\n< Serena >Even though it was to confirm the
extermination, bringing back a part of
the corpse...
\n< Serena >It's a bit too rough for my taste.
\n< Guild Master >The opponent is a monster, you know?
\n< Serena >That's precisely why.

\n< Serena >Precisely because of that, we must show those
monsters our pride as bearers of
civilization and protectors of culture.
\n< Serena >Isn't that right?
\n< Guild Master >.......

\n< Guild Master >Well... you can have your own principles and
beliefs.

\n< Guild Master >Anyway, it was decided. The request was to
bring back 10 goblin noses for a
contract of 3G, right?

\n< Guild Master >Since you didn't bring anything back, the
reward is also zero.

\n< Serena >Hmph. Well, it's my own choice. I have no
objections. I never relied on rewards to
begin with.

\n< Serena >However, in any case, we exterminated them and
helped people along the way.

\n< Serena >Make sure to keep a solid record of the
mission accomplishment.

\n< Guild Master >That's right. Normally, it should be recorded
as a failure...

\n< Guild Master >Since there were witnesses this time, let's
consider it a success. It's truly
unheard of. To have a request succeed
without any reward.

\n< Serena >So, we're only \V[2501] requests away from
fulfilling our promise.

\n< Serena >If we complete \V[2501] more requests, we
will issue a promissory note to the
eastern town.
\n< Serena >No doubt about it, right?

\n< Guild Master >No doubt about it. How many times have we
had this exchange...

\n< Serena >I'm in a hurry. No matter how many times I
check, it's not enough.
\n< Serena >Only \V[2501] more requests...
\n< Guild Master >And then, take this with you.
\n< Serena >What is this?

\n< Guild Master >It's the identification given to adventurers
who have completed their first job...
Well, it's like an ID card.

\n< Guild Master >Achievements and evaluations are also written here.
Don't lose it.

\n< Serena >So this is the proof of becoming a full-
fledged adventurer. Understood.
\n< Serena >Well.

\n< Serena >That's it for today. I need to rest up for
tomorrow.
\n< Serena >Eat, take a bath, sleep.

\n< Serena >Oh, right. I also need a spare ring.
Without this, I can't use my Sonic Fist.
\n< Serena >Geez, adventurers are unexpectedly busy.

\n< Serena >For now, let's find an inn. We'll do
everything after that.
依頼開始

\n< Guild Master >Yo, good morning. Have you gotten used to
this town?

\n< Serena >It's still the same day as yesterday. I
haven't gotten used to it yet, or maybe
I never will.
\n< Guild Master >Hehe, of course.
\n< Serena >Show me the quests.
依頼　序盤

\n< Guild Master >The request isn't finished yet, right? Come
back once you've completed the request.
イベント終了

Bar waitress en(v[2285]===0)
\n< Serena >Hey, what's up with this request?

\n< Guild Master >Hey hey, it doesn't seem like you've been
to the tavern, right?

\n< Serena >I went to the tavern the other day. I
didn't stay for long though.

\n< Guild Master >I see... Well, it's nothing important...
You're still young after all...

\n< Guild Master >If you don't understand on your own, maybe
this kind of job isn't suitable for a
young person like you, miss.

\n< Guild Master >Basically, it's a request to listen to the
customer's order and bring drinks and
food to their table. It's a request to
help out at the tavern.

\n< Serena >You want me to pretend to be a waitress?
Me, of all people?

\n< Guild Master >No one asked you to do it, miss. If you
don't like it, you don't have to do it.

\n< Serena >Hmmm. But it seems interesting. It's a job
that I wouldn't have the chance to do if
I stayed at the mansion my whole life.

\n< Serena >And... um, that fluttery outfit... I wonder if
I could wear that...

\n< Guild Master >I don't know which clothes, but I think
you'll be given a uniform. I'm not sure
if there's one that fits your size,
miss...

\n< Guild Master >By the way, the reward is based on
performance. It depends on how much you
can earn.
Take the job
I won't take it
Take on

\n< Serena >Very well. I will accept this request. I
will contact the client.

\n< Guild Master >In that case, take this paper as it is.
The conversation should go smoothly with
it.
\n< Serena >I see. Well then, I'll be going.
\n< Guild Master >Ah, be careful, okay?

\n< Guild Master >...Ah, that's not good. I feel like I'm
sending my child out for the first time.
イベント終了
Not take

Helping a farmer en(v[2282]===0)
\n< Serena >Help the farmer?
\n< Guild Master >What, are you interested in that kind of job?

\n< Serena >Regardless of whether it exists or not, it's too
vague and doesn't make sense.
\n< Serena >What kind of request is this?
\n< Guild Master >Um, this time... it's milking cows.

\n< Guild Master >Farmers are always short-handed, you know.
That's why we keep getting these
requests one after another.

\n< Guild Master >And most of the adventurers who take on
these requests are former farmers.

\n< Guild Master >For beginners who are just starting out and
don't have much money, they earn pocket
change by taking on these small
requests.
\n< Serena >Hmmm.
\n< Guild Master >That's why we only accept former farmers.

\n< Guild Master >This is a job that girls like you wouldn't
have any connection to.
\n< Serena >It's not like that.

\n< Serena >I'm used to dealing with livestock because
of my family's business.

\n< Serena >Well, I've never touched a cow before, but if
you just show me how to move my hands,
I'm confident that I can handle it
perfectly fine.

\n< Guild Master >Well, even though the reward is only 1G, are
you seriously considering taking on this
request?
Take on
Decline
Take on

\n< Serena >I'll take it. The reward may be small, but
I'm sure the evaluation will be high.

\n< Serena >This request is like a dream come true for
me right now.

\n< Guild Master >Well, even if you fail, it's not like someone
will die. And the former farmers are
also not available.

\n< Guild Master >It's better than postponing it until
tomorrow. Here, take the request
certificate and go.
\n< Serena >Should I show this to the client?

\n< Guild Master >Ah, the client is doing odd jobs in the
field, so if you show them that, they
should guide you to the workplace.
\n< Serena >Understood, it's the field. Well then, I'll be off.
\n< Guild Master >Ah, have a safe journey.
イベント終了

How to use the item

\n< Guild Master >First, you need to set the item you want to
use in the slot. To do that, open the
menu and select the slot option.

\n< Guild Master >Then, it will become the list screen of the
available registered items. Choose the
necessary item and register it in the
slot. With this, the preparation is
complete.

\n< Guild Master >During battle, you use items from the slot.
Select them with the 1, 2, or L/R
buttons, and activate the item's effect
with the slot use key.
No special need

Goblin extermination en(v[2284]===0)
\n< Serena >Did another goblin appear?

\n< Guild Master >Lately, there have been quite a few... I wonder
if some women have been captured
somewhere. We also have some missing
persons, you know...

\n< Serena >Do goblins increase when women are
captured?
\n< Guild Master >Well...
\n< Serena >....
\n< Guild Master >...Hmm...Ah...Well...What can I say? That's just how it is.
\n< Serena >？？？

\n< Guild Master >Anyway, the one that appeared this time is also
a stray.

\n< Guild Master >Even though they are just a few goblins, if
they come across women and children,
there is a possibility of losing their
lives.

\n< Guild Master >There's nothing better than getting rid of them
quickly. The reward for success is 3G.
Is it okay for you to accept this
request?
Accept
Decline
Take on

\n< Serena >Of course. There's no reason to refuse.
Let's accept that request.
\n< Guild Master >I'm counting on you.

\n< Guild Master >By the way, do you know how to use items
during battles, Miss?
I don't know
I know
I don't know
\n< Guild Master >Alright, then I'll give you a brief explanation.

\n< Guild Master >During battles, you can use items from the
slots. If you're using a keyboard, press
1 or 2. If you're using a gamepad, use
the L and R buttons to select and the
slot use button to activate the item's
effect.

\n< Guild Master >There are two slots. You need to register the
items you want to put in the slots in
advance from the menu screen.

\n< Guild Master >The method is simple. Just enter the slot
item in the menu screen, press the
register button, and select the item.

\n< Guild Master >Oh, by the way, it goes without saying, but
you can't register if you don't have any
items beforehand.

\n< Guild Master >Items are sold at the tool shop. Make sure to
buy at least one before going on an
adventure.

\n< Guild Master >If you're stingy even though it's
expensive, you'll end up paying an even
higher price.
\n< Serena >I roughly understand. Thank you, Master.
\n< Guild Master >Oh, come back safely.
I know

\n< Guild Master >I see. Well then, it seems like you'll be
fine. Come back safely.
イベント終了
Not take
イベント終了
Cancel

依頼　三つ終了後

\n< Guild Master >Don't you know the location? It's in the west
direction.
\n< Serena >I know.
Transporting luggage to the Minotaur Forest
Transporting goods to the Minotaur Forest
\n< Serena >...Hmm.
\n< Serena >Minotaur? This is...
\n< Guild Master >This is Erika's request. The reward is 1G.

\n< Guild Master >Can you deliver supplies and bento to the
forest camp?

\n< Serena >Are you leaving the supply to someone else?
Does that mean Erika-sama will be
confined to the forest?
\n< Guild Master >...Ricotte's older sister was killed by a Minotaur.

\n< Guild Master >Search for the enemy until your physical
limits, occasionally come down to the
town and take a little rest, then head
back to the forest.
\n< Serena >So there was such a situation...

\n< Guild Master >There's no one without circumstances.
Especially those who are adventurers.
\n< Guild Master >It's the same for you, right?
\n< Serena >Don't step in so much?
\n< Guild Master >Dealing with adults is like that.
\n< Guild Master >Well, we've gotten off track.

\n< Guild Master >The job is simply transporting supplies.
There shouldn't be much danger.
\n< Serena >How much is the amount of supplies?

\n< Guild Master >Just a small bag. It's mostly delivering
lunch.

\n< Serena >Understood. In that case, I'll take the job. Geez,
can't be helped.
\n< Guild Master >Hmph...
\n< Serena >What is it?

\n< Guild Master >...It's nothing. Their camp is always in the
same place.

\n< Guild Master >The location is in the western forest. I'll
give you a map, so follow it and go
there.
\n< Serena >Understood.

\n< Guild Master >This is the luggage... I don't think I need
to worry about you, but don't handle it
too roughly, okay?
イベント終了
依頼　ミノタウロス捜索終了後

\n< Guild Master >How about you have a little more fun,
laugh, and try acting like a child?
\n< Guild Master >Yo, miss, there's a message for you.
\n< Serena >Me?

\n< Guild Master >Did you save a woman from goblins? She
wants to thank you for that favor.

\n< Serena >I see. Please let her know that I don't
mind.

\n< Guild Master >You're not very friendly. The key to selling
products is friendliness and charm.
You'll only be adored for a limited
time, you know?

\n< Serena >Yeah... even if you say that, it's just my
nature. I don't have time.
\n< Serena >Master, show me the request instead.

\n< Guild Master >Well, the job that I could give you is gone
now.
\n< Serena >What?

\n< Guild Master >In a rural town like this, there aren't
originally that many requests. There are
actually more days without work.

\n< Guild Master >Well, it's better than having a mountain of
neglected requests, I suppose.
\n< Serena >It's not good for me. What should I do?

\n< Guild Master >In this case, you'll just have to wait.
But that doesn't mean you'll be left
waiting for days on end.

\n< Guild Master >The request to subdue the thieves is a bit
difficult. I'm thinking of sending
someone to check on the situation
soon...
\n< Serena >It doesn't matter even if it's today.

\n< Guild Master >Listen, the guild doesn't just issue requests
as they please.

\n< Guild Master >We operate within the limits of budget,
processing capacity, and regulations. We
strive for maximum efficiency within
those constraints.

\n< Guild Master >Ah well... Anyway, for today, go home. Or
rather, go. The hardworking girl like
you needs a break.

\n< Serena >...I see... So that's how it is. Did you
plan this?
\n< Serena >Mind your own business...

\n< Serena >...Well, it's fine. I've already completed one
request today. And about that woman...
come to think of it, I didn't ask for
her name...

\n< Serena >Anyway, it would be a lie to say that I wasn't
curious about that woman.

\n< Serena >Fine. I'll let you meddle in my affairs for
today.

\n< Serena >However, I would like you to prepare the request
by tomorrow.
\n< Guild Master >Ah, I understand, I understand.

\n< Guild Master >That person's house is on the south side of
town. Well, take your time and relax.

\n< Serena >Geez... Everyone treats me like a child just
because I'm a little short and spoils
me.
依頼　妊婦救助後

\n< Guild Master >The request isn't finished yet, right? Come
back once you've completed the request.
イベント終了

Orc Scout en(v[2283]===0)
\n< Serena >Orc? What kind of monster is this?

\n< Guild Master >What... You don't know about orcs? This is the
first time someone has asked for an
explanation.

\n< Guild Master >Well... You can think of it as a goblin that
has grown up in appearance. It seems to
be a different race though.
\n< Serena >Hmmm.

\n< Guild Master >They are muscular and their nature can be
described as ferocious. They are
extremely aggressive monsters. They
willingly attack people.

\n< Guild Master >So, it seems that orc scouts are wandering
around this area. Please defeat them
before it becomes a big problem, or at
least drive them away.

\n< Serena >Scouts? So that means there must be a main
force somewhere.

\n< Guild Master >I'm not sure. We don't know the habits of
monsters. But before a large outbreak of
orcs, small groups tend to appear.

\n< Guild Master >I don't know if they call for their
comrades or if they breed, but we call
them scouts, anyway.
\n< Serena >Hmmm... What about the location and number?

\n< Guild Master >It's in the eastern forest. There are two of
them. It seems like they are just
wandering around for now.

\n< Guild Master >The reward is 1G per orc. With a successful
completion bonus, it's 2G. In total,
it's 4G. So, what do you think? Will you
give it a try?
I'll do it
Not doing it
Take it

\n< Serena >Hmmm... I can't just leave it alone. I'll take
it. I'll accept it...
\n< Guild Master >What is it?

\n< Serena >If they are said to be such ferocious
opponents, I would like to investigate
more about the enemy.

\n< Serena >Do we have any books or documents? Even
reports from previous encounters would
be fine.

\n< Guild Master >Ah... We don't have any books, but there is
someone in town who is knowledgeable
about that kind of thing.
\n< Serena >Oh.

\n< Guild Master >His name is Tomo, but everyone calls him
the Monster Doctor. Well, it's partly
just teasing.

\n< Guild Master >I wonder how many people in this town can
say they are knowledgeable about
monsters.
\n< Serena >...The conversation doesn't flow well.

\n< Guild Master >...Tomo is what you would call a weirdo. There
are times when I can't really understand
what he's thinking.

\n< Guild Master >It doesn't seem like he's a bad person or
a heretic...

\n< Serena >So you mean someone who is difficult to
get along with.

\n< Guild Master >Ah... Well, maybe I actually get along with
you better than I thought.

\n< Serena >What do you mean? Well, nevermind. I'm
going.
イベント終了
I won't do it
イベント終了
Distribution of Poison en(v[2288]===0)
\n< Serena >Poison is not a gentle request.

\n< Guild Master >Ah, I heard it's been popular lately. I
haven't seen it around here much though.
\n< Serena >Poison is popular?

\n< Guild Master >Don't you know? It's a potion for
inheritance.

\n< Guild Master >Ah, I'm in need of money. If only my
father-in-law would die, I would inherit
his fortune. Oh, perfect timing--.
\n< Serena >Enough. So, what about it?

\n< Guild Master >There seems to be some informants. It seems
that there are people who want to bring
it into this town.

\n< Guild Master >It's not suitable for our peaceful town. I
would like you to take it away.

\n< Guild Master >So, this will be a request from the guild.
Actually, me...

\n< Serena >Should I just go in and defeat everyone on the
scene?

\n< Guild Master >Ah, it's perfect for you, miss. A small fry
who doesn't even have any secrets worth
washing. Please go ahead and take care
of it to your heart's content.

\n< Serena >I don't mind, but if it's just small fry
like that, no matter how much we crush
them, won't it only be a temporary
solution?

\n< Serena >If you want to stop the influx of poison,
we must cut off the source.

\n< Guild Master >If we could do that, it would be no
trouble. Well, we'll take care of that
later.

\n< Guild Master >I'll pay 4G as a reward. Will you take the
job?
Accept
I won't take it

\n< Serena >Alright. I'll take the job.

\n< Guild Master >Thank you. This is the request form. It also
has the location where they will pass
written on it.

\n< Guild Master >The location is off the eastern highway.
It's perfect because it's out of sight
from people.

\n< Guild Master >They're not much in terms of quantity or
quality, but there's always a chance of
something unexpected. Be careful, okay?

\n< Serena >If I have determined that I will be fine,
then you should leave it to me. Well
then, I'll be going.

\n< Serena >Unicorn.
\n< Guild Master >What's wrong, miss? Are you frozen in place?
\n< Serena >Th-this request... I will... take this request.
\n< Guild Master >Oh, okay.

\n< Serena >Give me the documents. The request
certificate... quickly!

\n< Guild Master >It's rare to see you so calm and composed...
Here, this is the document.

\n< Guild Master >It seems that the client is at the inn, so
please ask them directly for more
details.
\n< Serena >Ah, thank you, Master. I'm off!
\n< Guild Master >Hmmm?
\n< Serena >Clue, I finally got a clue!

\n< Serena >As I thought, there was no mistake in
coming here. They said the location is
at the inn. I must go and hear the story
as soon as possible...!
Cancel

第一部最終依頼　導入
\n< Serena >Master, this is...
\n< Guild Master >....
Emergency Rescue Request
Emergency Rescue Request
Rescue Target: Erika. Rin Route.
\n< Serena >What's going on?
\n< Guild Master >It's just as it looks.

\n< Guild Master >That idiot took on a request to subdue the
thieves, but it seems they failed. They
got caught, apparently.

\n< Guild Master >The woman that Erika rescued came to
deliver a message. Originally, the
request was to rescue this woman.

\n< Guild Master >It's not helpful if you get caught in
exchange...

\n< Guild Master >...Adventurers sometimes face situations like this.
That's why it's important to deposit
money at the guild as a precaution in
case you mess up.

\n< Guild Master >If I don't come back, please use this
money to request a rescue.

\n< Guild Master >That's why the client for this request is also
Erika.

\n< Serena >Enough with the preamble. Let me hear the
situation.
\n< Guild Master >Are you taking on the request?
\n< Serena >Of course.

\n< Guild Master >This request is different from the ones
before. It's against humans, and there
are a lot of them.

\n< Guild Master >Moreover, you need to infiltrate their base and
rescue the hostages. There's no way you
can do stealth operations, kid.
\n< Serena >That's right.

\n< Guild Master >That means you'll have to fight the thieves
head- on.

\n< Guild Master >They're just country thieves. They don't have
impressive equipment, but a group of
armed humans is still a formidable
opponent.

\n< Guild Master >Even experienced and accomplished
adventurers usually try to avoid
fighting.

\n< Serena >But Erika went to fight. To save that
woman.

\n< Guild Master >Ah, because she's an idiot. To her, the
opponent is someone she doesn't even
know the name of. I told her to abandon
it.

\n< Serena >Are you planning to say the same thing to
me?
\n< Guild Master >....

\n< Serena >Don't make that face, Master. In short, as
long as I'm stronger than all the
thieves.
\n< Serena >I have confidence in that.
\n< Guild Master >...Has your determination not changed?

\n< Serena >Even if I can't take on the request here,
I'll go on my own.
\n< Guild Master >Understood.

\n< Guild Master >In that case, let me make a request as
well.
\n< Guild Master >Please, help that person.
\n< Serena >Leave it to me.

\n< Guild Master >We're going to infiltrate the thieves'
hideout. Naturally, we'll have to
confront them.

\n< Guild Master >But it's not possible to go. If it turns
into a battle, Erika will naturally
become a hostage.

\n< Guild Master >If that's the case, no matter how strong
the young lady is, it's a hopeless
situation.

\n< Guild Master >That's why securing Erika is the priority.
Head straight towards Erika and rescue
her.

\n< Guild Master >And then, take down the approaching
thieves. If we have to fight, this is
the order.
\n< Serena >That's only natural.

\n< Guild Master >The thieves have made the ruins in the
forest their base.

\n< Guild Master >Whether it's an ancient temple or a fortress,
it's not that big of a box.

\n< Guild Master >The ruins are built as if they are carrying
steep cliffs on their backs. The
surroundings are also hilly, giving it a
balance as if standing in a hollow.
\n< Serena >Natural fortress, huh.

\n< Guild Master >It's not that impressive. It's just a slope
that you can climb by walking normally.

\n< Guild Master >The reason they made this place their base
is probably because they wanted to hide
and sneak around rather than anything
else.

\n< Serena >Isn't it actually convenient for the invading
side?

\n< Guild Master >I suppose so. Especially the cliff side
is not well guarded. This is Erika's
estimation, though.

\n< Guild Master >Their plan was to use ropes to quickly
descend from the cliff side, enter the
building from the rooftop, and rescue
the hostages.

\n< Guild Master >This rope is rigged with a pulley and a
weight. When you light the fuse from
below, the weight that is fixed above
will drop and the rope will rapidly wind
up.

\n< Guild Master >After rescuing the hostages, we were supposed
to go back to the rooftop once more and
use this mechanism to escape all at
once. The plan was to then flee to the
town.

\n< Guild Master >Even though they could enter from anywhere
around, they chose to use the cliff.
They must have planned to catch the
thieves off guard.
\n< Serena >But we failed.
\n< Guild Master >No, we didn't use it in the first place.

\n< Guild Master >It seems like they found out that a woman
was taken outside and hastily took her
back. According to the woman's account.

\n< Guild Master >Unexpected actions... Did they think it was an
opportunity?... No, they probably just
couldn't stand by and watch...
\n< Serena >Lord Erika...

\n< Guild Master >So the woman escaped, but that person was
caught.

\n< Guild Master >Fortunately or unfortunately, thanks to that, the
plan that Erika was supposed to use is
still intact.

\n< Guild Master >It means that he himself will be saved by
the plan he came up with.

\n< Guild Master >If we do this right, we can minimize the
battle with the thieves.

\n< Serena >That's good, but from what I've heard, it
seems quite elaborate... In other words,
it seems like a conspicuous trap.

\n< Serena >Isn't it possible that after Lady Erika was
captured, the rope was found and
discarded?

\n< Guild Master >Ah, of course that's an option. But if
that's the case, then you should just
come back for now.
\n< Serena >That's right. It was a foolish question.

\n< Guild Master >At that time, we'll have to rethink our
strategy. But well, for now, let's
continue assuming certain things.

\n< Guild Master >The ruins have a three-layer structure.
However, according to the woman, the
first and third floors are heavily
deteriorated and hardly used.

\n< Guild Master >It seems that the thieves' sleeping
quarters, storage of loot, and the
prison for holding the woman are all
located on the second floor.

\n< Guild Master >Perhaps Erika is also captured in this second
floor prison. However, it seems that
even the woman doesn't have a grasp of
the structure inside the building.

\n< Guild Master >We need to actually infiltrate and search
for the location of the prison.

\n< Serena >If we know just that much, it's enough. We
should infiltrate from the rooftop and
search the uninhabited third floor for
Lady Erika.

\n< Guild Master >Ah, but even if we manage to find Erika
successfully, don't rush to rescue her
immediately.
\n< Serena >Why?

\n< Guild Master >It's a common practice among thieves. If
they're about to be captured, there's
always someone whose role is to kill the
hostage.
\n< Serena >Despicable...

\n< Guild Master >So, find that person first. You should be
able to tell right away since they'll be
carrying a weapon.

\n< Serena >That's a strange way of putting it. Aren't
other thieves like that too?
\n< Guild Master >Well...probably not.

\n< Guild Master >Thieves, robbers, rapists... Since coming to
this town, that person has been taking
care of those scoundrels one by one.

\n< Guild Master >There were a few requests involving thieves
as well. Although it was a side job of
searching for the infamous monster, the
damage inflicted upon them should have
been considerable.

\n< Guild Master >If we capture Erika, and find out what
those vengeful thieves are up to in the
prison cell...

\n< Serena >So they're torturing and killing her...!
You bastards...!

\n< Guild Master >If they killed Erika, they would have
displayed her dead body as a warning in
an open field.

\n< Guild Master >Regardless of the situation, the fact that it
hasn't happened yet means that person is
still alive.

\n< Guild Master >However, you should think that there isn't much
time left.

\n< Serena >Don't waste a moment. Let's head to the scene
immediately.
\n< Guild Master >Take this too.

\n< Serena >Healing potions, bandages... Ah, all of these
would be necessary for Lady Erika, I
suppose.

\n< Serena >What about these potions? I've never seen
these bottles before. Skull marks...?

\n< Guild Master >That's also for Erika. It's a powerful
medicine, so don't ever drink it, okay?

\n< Serena >Do you think I wouldn't notice?
Understood. I'll take care of it.

\n< Guild Master >Ah, that's all I want to give you. The
quickest way to the thieves' hideout is
by cutting through the western forest.

\n< Serena >Yes, understood... I promise to bring that
kind and meddlesome person back here
without fail.
\n< Guild Master >Miss... I'm counting on you, Erika.
第一部最終依頼　導入

\n< Guild Master >If you're going to the hideout of the
thief gang, go straight through the
western forest. It will likely turn into
a series of battles, so make sure to
prepare yourself properly.

events.note: 依頼の種類とかを教えてくれる

parameters: 序盤依頼三つ進行中

\n< Adventurer >The average daily earnings of a laborer are
about 1G. Adventurers risk their lives
and earn an income of 5 to 10G.

\n< Adventurer >Sometimes I wonder, which one of us values our
lives more highly?
ミノタウロスの探索進行中

\n< Adventurer >Transporting supplies, huh? This one will do for
today.

\n< Adventurer >Did you know? Adventurers were originally
merchants, you know.

\n< Adventurer >It seems that the predecessor of the
Adventurer's Guild was the Merchant
Guild. In other words, transportation is
the true essence of being an adventurer.
ミノタウロス捜索後

\n< Adventurer >It seems like the safety in the eastern
town is deteriorating year by year.

\n< Adventurer >Where people gather, money, illness, and
crime come along.

\n< Adventurer >For a king who relies on his subjects, as
long as they pay their taxes, anything
else should be fine, I suppose.
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中

\n< Adventurer >Hey, you've gotten the hang of it, haven't
you?

\n< Adventurer >Working is a good thing, no matter what. Even
the great scholar says so.
依頼三つ終了・フリーモード進行中

\n< Adventurer >The bridge closure is the lord's order.
They said that young people were
crossing the river one after another, so
they hurriedly closed it off.

\n< Adventurer >Why do all of them willingly want to go to
the city?
第一部ラスト　冒険者の救助開始前
\n< Adventurer >Erika, seriously...

\n< Adventurer >So you mean... as a thief... in other
words...

\n< Adventurer >Ah, damn it...! But a rescue request like
this is...!
第一部ラスト　冒険者の救助開始後

\n< Adventurer >Did you accept the rescue request... from a
girl like you...
\n< Adventurer >....

events.name: 冒険者女性
events.note: 女性冒険者の心得を教えてくれる

parameters: 序盤依頼三つ進行中
\n< Female Adventurer >What? Lost?

\n< Female Adventurer >There's nothing interesting here. I'm just
chasing after grasshoppers with my
friends.
序盤依頼三つ進行中

\n< Female Adventurer >Goblin extermination? Wow, so you took on the
request. I guess that makes you an
adventurer...

\n< Female Adventurer >Take a bath right after it's done. Those
goblins seriously stink. Well, I guess
that goes without saying, right?
序盤依頼三つ進行中

\n< Female Adventurer >Have you seen any goblin children? I hope
you've properly exterminated them.

\n< Female Adventurer >If they continue to live, they will only
bring forth sin and suffering.

\n< Female Adventurer >It's an act of mercy and virtue to dispose
of them while they're still children.
ミノタウロスの探索進行中

\n< Female Adventurer >Ah, I'm going on that muscle gorilla's
errand.
\n< Female Adventurer >What are you doing holed up in the forest...
ミノタウロス捜索後
\n< Female Adventurer >Minotaur? No, I haven't seen it.

\n< Female Adventurer >So you're saying it was repelled right
here between the forest? It's a close
call story, but well, it's hard to
believe.
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中

\n< Female Adventurer >Hey there. Looks like I'm getting used to
this adventurer job.
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中
\n< Female Adventurer >Orcs...! Are we going to deal with them...?

\n< Female Adventurer >They're all muscular and bulky, like muscle
monsters, right? And they're green too.
It's physically repulsive. I'll pass.
\n< Female Adventurer >At least put on some pants!
依頼三つ終了・フリーモード進行中

\n< Female Adventurer >Didn't you find it strange that there were no
gathering requests?

\n< Female Adventurer >It's because I've been taking on every
single one of them. As soon as they
appear. In a matter of seconds.

\n< Female Adventurer >Actually, recently I've been stockpiling various
medicinal herbs and delivering them as
soon as I accept the request...!
第一部ラスト　冒険者の救助開始前
\n< Female Adventurer >I heard they caught a muscle gorilla?

\n< Female Adventurer >Well, my condolences. Even if you survive,
you'll probably be permanently disabled.

\n< Female Adventurer >That's why we women have to carefully choose
our requests.

\n< Female Adventurer >...What's with that look? If a woman gets caught,
you can imagine what happens, right?

events.name: 冒険者男
events.note: 冒険時の注意事項やらを教えてくれる

parameters: 宿を出てから道具屋に行くまで

\n< Adventurer >Make sure to store potion-like items in an
easily accessible place, okay?

\n< Adventurer >If you plan to use them during battle,
make sure to utilize the slots. If you
don't set them up before the adventure,
you won't be able to use them when the
time comes.
ミノタウロスの探索進行中

\n< Adventurer >In our guild, there's a blonde adventurer
named Ricotte. Despite being a woman,
she was unexpectedly strong.

\n< Adventurer >She goes on business trips and adventures
all over the place, so she's become a
bit of a celebrity.

\n< Adventurer >However, just the other day, I fought and died
against a monster called a Minotaur.
Right here in this town.

\n< Adventurer >I often wonder what being an adventurer
is all about. No matter how strong you
are, when it's time to die, it happens
in an instant.
ミノタウロス捜索後

\n< Adventurer >It seems like Erika and the Master have
known each other for a long time.

\n< Adventurer >There must have been some connection between
them through Ricott. Well, it seems like
both of them don't want to talk about
Ricott.
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中

\n< Adventurer >If you're an adventurer, it's only natural
to experience failures. In fact,
failures are more common than successes.

\n< Adventurer >I heard that even top-class adventurers
have a success rate of only about 60%.

\n< Adventurer >For us who are below third-rate, it's only
natural to be even worse. In that case,
we have to think about how to deal with
failures.

\n< Adventurer >Even if you fail, life doesn't end. It won't
end. Remember that well.
妊婦の話後　後半依頼三つ進行中

\n< Adventurer >There are still few violent monsters around
here. Thanks to the river to the east
acting as a breakwater.

\n< Adventurer >Once you cross the river, it's like a
completely different world. The monsters
become ferocious, and the humans who
fight against them also become
ferocious.

\n< Adventurer >They say that they don't have any trouble
with work because of that. But I prefer
a laid-back life of poverty, it suits me
better.
依頼三つ終了・フリーモード進行中

\n< Adventurer >Thieves can generally be classified into three
types: former mercenaries, former
nobles, and former adventurers.

\n< Adventurer >The thieves around here are a bunch of
former adventurers. Among them, there
are some worthless ones who were kicked
out from Kawahigashi.

\n< Adventurer >However, when humans gather, they become a
threat in themselves. The guild here is
not enough to deal with them.

\n< Adventurer >The days of waiting with bated breath for
the lord to come and subdue them,
well...
第一部ラスト　冒険者の救助開始前

\n< Adventurer >It seems being a lord is tough these days.
This thing called gold coins seems to be
the cause of it.

\n< Adventurer >In the past, having abundant crops was
considered the power of a lord. But gold
coins don't just sprout from rice
fields. They're not part of a lord's
domain, you know.

\n< Adventurer >The world's rules have changed from wheat
to gold coins.

\n< Adventurer >So from now on, the world will no longer
be dominated by nobles. It will be the
era of merchants and cities, the so-
called third estate... or so they say.
第一部ラスト　冒険者の救助開始後
\n< Adventurer >Wasn't the young lady close with Erika?

\n< Adventurer >Well, it might be pointless advice, but I'll
say it just in case.

\n< Adventurer >An adventurer who can't abandon their
friends won't live long.

\n< Adventurer >It's our motto... Ah, I know, I know. You
don't have to ask.
\n< Serena >I have no business here.
\n< Serena >It's a bag.

\n< Serena >The contents are empty. I suppose you can
put money in here and give it to
adventurers as a reward.

\n< Serena >...Come to think of it, this bag itself might
have a decent price.

\n< Serena >The price of the bag might be deducted from
the reward. It doesn't really matter to
me though.
\n< Serena >Here's the request document.

\n< Serena >If you take this and go to the client's
place, it will serve as proof that I am
the contractor for the request.

\n< Serena >After the completion of the request, I will
receive the client's signature and bring
it back. It's a completely rational
system.
\n< Serena >Scroll... No, it's just a piece of paper.

\n< Serena >It seems like this is something you can
use to write and make notes on the map.
Of course, it's not free.
\n< Serena >Made of sturdy parchment.
\n< Serena >It's a bag.

\n< Serena >I'm taking out coins from inside and
counting or looking at them.
\n< Serena >I feel like you shouldn't stare so much.
\n< Serena >I have a request.
\n< Serena >Delivery request to a distant place.
\n< Serena >It's a request that I have no use for.
\n< Serena >I have a request.
\n< Serena >Mercenary recruitment.

\n< Serena >It seems that we, as the Adventurer's
Guild, are organizing a mercenary corps
to be dispatched to the battlefield.

\n< Serena >This is a request that has nothing to do
with me in any way.
\n< Serena >I have a request.
\n< Serena >Bounty hunting.

\n< Serena >It's not something I know how much time it
will take to explore. I'll pass on this.
\n< Serena >I have a request.

\n< Serena >Babysitter. Someone with experience in childbirth
and good milk production.

\n< Serena >Why would such a request be made to the
Adventurer's Guild...? Is there someone
who would take it? It's impossible for
me, though.
\n< Serena >Here's the map.

\n< Serena >This is a rough... I mean, really rough map
of the area.

\n< Serena >Detailed maps are classified for territorial
defense purposes. That's why there is a
demand even for these vague maps.
\n< Serena >It's a barrel.

\n< Serena >When I pushed it with my hand, it moved a
little. It seems empty inside.
\n< Serena >Here's some alcohol.

\n< Serena >I don't really like alcohol. It just
makes me feel sick.

\n< Serena >I think it's great to be born in a place
with good water. The water around here
is also good.
\n< Serena >Let's not get involved with the counter.

\n< Serena >I don't think we'll get scolded, but I'm
sure it will trouble the Master.
